summary: Oh just thought of another thing that could potentially be really short. I saw that post you reblogged about tony stark as a...
question: Oh just thought of another thing that could potentially be really short. I saw that post you reblogged about tony stark as a puppy and how about peter bringing home one of those one day and excitedly shoving him in tonys face like "look tony i named him after you" and tony as the sort of dad is absolutely speechless. Its up to you if you write it to make him love it or hate it not that hed ever be able to say no to peter
answer:
I had lots of fun writing this prompt! Thank you for sending it in, and I hope you like it as much as I do :D

“Parker, wanna stay after class to help with the prom decorations?”

“Sorry, MJ, but I’ve got a meeting with Mr. Stark. I’ve gotta go after,” Peter apologized. He wanted to spend some time with her, especially since his spidey duties kept him busy most of the time, but he couldn’t blow off his mentor, not today of all days.

“Sure, whatever,” she waved him off. “Have fun, nerd.”

She gave him a slight, barely there smile and Peter felt himself fall in love all over again. He smiled broadly and waved at her before turning around and going to his next and last class of the day.

He kept counting the minutes and glancing at his watch every other minute throughout the class, excitement coursing through his veins. He couldn’t get out of his seat fast enough when the bell rang, and he sprinted down the hallways, jumping the fence with ease and rushing to his favourite alley to put on the suit and get…something else too.

“Hey there, buddy. Didn’t think you’d still be here, but I sure am glad you are,” Peter cooed at the tiny, fluffy, white pomeranian in his hands. The small puppy started wiggling his tail like crazy, licking his fingers with abandon and yelping tiny, adorable barks.

“Is someone excited to see me? Huh? Of course you are, you beautiful little thing. Such a good boy, yes! The best boy!”

Peter would have noticed the strangeness of the sight of Spider-Man playing with a puppy and cooing at it in an alley, but he was too excited and distracted to care.

“Let’s put you somewhere safe, yes? There you go, all done,” he placed the pup in his school bag, then swung it over his shoulders carefully and took off towards the Compound.

It didn’t take him long to get there, mainly because he was distracted the entire time thinking about what name to pick for the dog. For whatever reason the little guy reminded him of Mr. Stark so by the time the Compound came into view he decided to call him Tony.

The window he usually swung in through opened the moment F.R.I.D.A.Y. detected his presence. He landed on the floor with ease, only stumbling once before he righted himself, and he had a happy smile on his gave when he removed his mask and set his school bag down carefully.

“Welcome, Peter,” F.R.I.D.A.Y. greeted him.

“Hey there, Fri. Where’s Mr. Stark?” Peter asked while he deactivated the suit and put it away in the bag, being extra careful to take Tony out without F.RI.D.A.Y. noticing.

“Boss is right around the corner. He’s coming in 5, 4, 3, 2-”

“Sup, kid,” Mr. Stark said as he rounded the corner, coffee mug in hand (the “No.1 mentor” mug Peter had had made for the man’s birthday). He headed straight for the coffee machine for a refill, and didn’t turn to look at the teen until a steaming mug of fresh coffee was sitting safely in his hands.

Meanwhile, Peter had turned to face him, Tony gingerly held in his hands behind his back. He knew he looked suspicious but he had to test the waters first and then the big reveal.

“What you got there?” Mr. Stark asked after he took a sip of coffee. Peter cringed at the sight, still unable to understand why anyone would drink depression in liquid form (“Life is bitter enough as it is, Mr. Stark, why drink it too?”).

“Weeeeeeeeell,” Peter began, “I didn’t know if I should bring him here or not but he was still there when I got off school and I couldn’t just leave him alone! May said we can’t keep him because of her allergy but I was hoping you’d be down!”

Mr. Stark blinked once before he set the mug down on the counter and raised an eyebrow.

“And who is he, exactly?”

Peter smiled sheepishly and brought his hands in front of him, taking Tony with him and holding him out for Mr. Stark to see.

“What do you think?”

“Why am I even surprised anymore?” He didn’t sound angry, but Peter still feared he might get a scolding. To his surprise, when he dared look at the man’s face, Mr. Stark was smiling in the softest, most fond way he had seen him smile since Pepper got her first ultrasound. Peter didn’t know what to do with all of this emotion.

“Soooooo does that mean I can keep him? Here, I mean?”

“Sure, kid,” Mr. Stark laughed and took a few steps forward to pet the little buddy. “What’s his name?”

“This is Tony,” Peter thrust the dog into Mr. Stark’s arms and smiled.

“Tony, huh?” his mentor mused while scratching Tony behind the ears. “Has a nice ring to it, doesn’t it, Tony?”

They played a bit with Tony before leaving Happy on babysitting duty while they went to the workshop.

“Get a girl next time and name her Virginia, would you, kid?” Mr. Stark said on the way to the workshop and Peter couldn’t help but burst out laughing.

Peter smiled sheepishly and brought his hands in front of him, taking Tony with him and holding him out for Mr. Stark to see.

“What do you think?”

“Why am I even surprised anymore?” He didn’t sound angry, but Peter still feared he might get a scolding. To his surprise, when he dared look at the man’s face, Mr. Stark was smiling in the softest, most fond way he had seen him smile since Pepper got her first ultrasound. Peter didn’t know what to do with all of this emotion.

“Soooooo does that mean I can keep him? Here, I mean?”

“Sure, kid,” Mr. Stark laughed and took a few steps forward to pet the little buddy. “What’s his name?”

“This is Tony,” Peter thrust the dog into Mr. Stark’s arms and smiled.

“Tony, huh?” his mentor mused while scratching Tony behind the ears. “Has a nice ring to it, doesn’t it, Tony?”

They played a bit with Tony before leaving Happy on babysitting duty while they went to the workshop.

“Get a girl next time and name her Virginia, would you, kid?” Mr. Stark said on the way to the workshop and Peter couldn’t help but burst out laughing.

“Parker, wanna stay after class to help with the prom decorations?”

“Sorry, MJ, but I’ve got a meeting with Mr. Stark. I’ve gotta go after,” Peter apologized. He wanted to spend some time with her, especially since his spidey duties kept him busy most of the time, but he couldn’t blow off his mentor, not today of all days.

“Sure, whatever,” she waved him off. “Have fun, nerd.”

She gave him a slight, barely there smile and Peter felt himself fall in love all over again. He smiled broadly and waved at her before turning around and going to his next and last class of the day.

He kept counting the minutes and glancing at his watch every other minute throughout the class, excitement coursing through his veins. He couldn’t get out of his seat fast enough when the bell rang, and he sprinted down the hallways, jumping the fence with ease and rushing to his favourite alley to put on the suit and get…something else too.

“Hey there, buddy. Didn’t think you’d still be here, but I sure am glad you are,” Peter cooed at the tiny, fluffy, white pomeranian in his hands. The small puppy started wiggling his tail like crazy, licking his fingers with abandon and yelping tiny, adorable barks.

“Is someone excited to see me? Huh? Of course you are, you beautiful little thing. Such a good boy, yes! The best boy!”
